io.github.nucleuspowered.nucleus.api.nucleusdata

Interface Kit


  • public interface Kit
    Represents a kit in Nucleus.

    Note that this kit requires explicit saving, see save()

      • ignoresPermission

        boolean ignoresPermission()
        Gets whether redeeming this kit will ignore the permission checks.

        Specifically, this is for when separate kit permissions are turned on in the Nucleus config, if this is true, this kit will never require a separate permission to redeem.

        Returns:
        true if this kit does not require a permission to redeem.

      • setIgnoresPermission

        Kit setIgnoresPermission(boolean ignoresPermission)

        Parameters:
        ignoresPermission - Whether to ignore separate permission checks
        Returns:
        This Kit, for chaining.

      • isHiddenFromList

        boolean isHiddenFromList()
        Gets whether this kit is hidden from the /kits list (except for those with permission to view it).

        If hidden, a player won't be able to tab complete to this either, but can still redeem the kit.

        Returns:
        Whether the kit is hidden from the /kits list and tab complete.
